{
  "texts": [
    "Second, our systematic review included only a basic assessment of the risk of bias, differentiating between expertled, collaborative and comprehensive guidelines by analyzing the rigor of the consensus process.",
    "While risk of bias assessment tools developed for systematic reviews of observational or interventional trials 24, 25 would not be appropriate for a methodological review, an in-depth analysis with a custom, methods-centered tool 26 could have provided more insights on the specific shortcomings of the included guidelines.",
    "Third, we acknowledge the potential limitation of the context-agnostic nature of our summary of consensus items.",
    "While we intentionally adopted a generalized approach to create broadly applicable findings, we recognize that this lack of nuance may result in our findings being of varying applicability depending on the specific subject domain.",
    "Fourth, this systematic review has limitations related to guideline selection and classification and limited generalizability."
  ]
}